# api-endpoints

API Routes for Meeting and Document Management (Importance: 85/100)

Key Endpoints:

1. Meeting Signal Management
```
/api/meetings/{meeting_id}/signals
/api/meetings/{meeting_id}/extract
```
- Extracts structured signals from meeting content
- Categorizes signals into decisions, actions, blockers, risks
- Associates signals with sprint context
- Handles signal approval workflows

2. Document Processing 
```
/api/documents/process
/api/documents/{doc_id}/signals
```
- Converts documents into meeting-compatible signal format
- Implements document-to-meeting signal promotion
- Manages document version tracking with signal context

3. Knowledge Graph Integration
```
/api/graph/signals
/api/graph/relationships
```
- Creates graph nodes from meeting signals
- Establishes relationships between signals across meetings
- Maintains DIKW hierarchy connections

4. Sprint Context Management
```
/api/sprint/signals
/api/sprint/archive
```
- Tracks signals within sprint boundaries
- Handles sprint transition signal archival
- Manages signal state transitions during sprint changes

5. Accountability Tracking
```
/api/signals/waiting
/api/signals/blocked
```
- Tracks signal dependencies and blockers
- Manages waiting-for items with context
- Updates accountability status across meetings

Business-Specific Endpoints:
- Signal extraction and categorization
- Sprint context association 
- Knowledge graph relationship management
- Accountability status tracking

